Why would Assad,
who's essentially,

00:03:00.980 --> 00:03:04.284
this is the Alawite kingdom,
and he's supported by Iran.

00:03:04.284 --> 00:03:07.353
Why would he unleash a Sunni

00:03:07.353 --> 00:03:09.889 align:start size:88% position:13%
fundamentalist
terrorist organization?

00:03:09.889 --> 00:03:13.493
Wouldn't they be
his mortal enemy?

00:03:13.493 --> 00:03:14.994
- No.

00:03:14.994 --> 00:03:17.764
He wanted from the start
of the Syrian revolution,

00:03:17.764 --> 00:03:19.966 line:0%
he had a strategy and plan.

00:03:19.966 --> 00:03:23.369 line:0%
He wanted the free world to
see that it's only a choice

00:03:23.369 --> 00:03:26.339 align:start size:84% position:16% line:0%
between an evil
terrorist organization

00:03:26.339 --> 00:03:28.408 line:0%
and an evil dictatorship.

00:03:28.408 --> 00:03:31.511 align:start size:84% position:16%
And he assumed that
the world would choose

00:03:31.511 --> 00:03:33.479
the lesser of the two evils,

00:03:33.479 --> 00:03:36.015 align:start size:88% position:13%
and they would choose
Assad to cooperate with.

00:03:36.015 --> 00:03:38.651 align:start size:88% position:13%
Luckily, the free world
refused to do this,

00:03:38.651 --> 00:03:40.220
and they understood the game,

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:42.589
and they stood by
the Syrian people.

00:03:42.589 --> 00:03:44.757
- Are you concerned?

00:03:44.757 --> 00:03:46.926
You know, I think the
sympathies of the world

00:03:46.926 --> 00:03:51.664
are with this coalition of
people who just want freedom,

00:03:51.664 --> 00:03:52.932
they just want to be left alone,

00:03:52.932 --> 00:03:54.267
they just want to
live their lives.

00:03:54.267 --> 00:03:58.204 align:start size:88% position:13%
How do you combat Assad
is backed by Iran,

00:03:58.204 --> 00:04:00.974
and in some ways
backed by Russia?

00:04:02.475 --> 00:04:05.178 align:start size:84% position:16%
ISIS, ISIL is backed
by maybe Assad.

00:04:05.178 --> 00:04:07.614 align:start size:97% position:3%
Maybe they're getting money
from some of the other

00:04:07.614 --> 00:04:11.050
more fundamentalist
regimes in the area.

00:04:11.050 --> 00:04:14.821 align:start size:88% position:13%
How is a group like this
going to defeat them

00:04:15.688 --> 00:04:18.391
and create something stable?

00:04:18.391 --> 00:04:21.160 align:start size:84% position:16% line:0%
- Mainly by our will,
and our patience.

00:04:21.160 --> 00:04:24.964 align:start position:0% line:0%
This is the future of our kids,
our granddaughters and son.

00:04:24.964 --> 00:04:27.734 line:0%
We have been fighting
them since 40 years,

00:04:27.734 --> 00:04:31.037
and the world has kept silent.

00:04:31.037 --> 00:04:32.305
Nobody moved.

00:04:32.305 --> 00:04:34.307
They moved only against ISIS.

00:04:34.307 --> 00:04:37.277
Why they didn't move and
do anything for Assad?

00:04:37.277 --> 00:04:38.711
- [Jon] Mm-hmm.

00:04:38.711 --> 00:04:41.214 align:start size:97% position:3%
- But we, the people of
Syria will carry on our fight

00:04:41.214 --> 00:04:44.083
and will fight until we
win back our freedom,

00:04:44.083 --> 00:04:48.755
and we'll achieve our quest
into a democratic society.

00:04:48.755 --> 00:04:49.822
- How would you...

00:04:49.822 --> 00:04:50.857
(applause)

00:04:50.857 --> 00:04:53.459
I wish you very well with that.

00:04:56.763 --> 00:04:59.399
So now a coalition has formed

00:04:59.399 --> 00:05:01.434
that they are going to
do strategic air strikes

00:05:01.434 --> 00:05:04.771
that they believe
will weaken ISIS.

00:05:04.771 --> 00:05:07.073
Will they weaken them
to the extent that,

00:05:07.073 --> 00:05:09.208
is this some sort
of round robin?

00:05:09.208 --> 00:05:13.179
Does the free Syrians have
to fight and defeat ISIS

00:05:13.179 --> 00:05:15.481
and then take on Assad?

00:05:15.481 --> 00:05:19.385
Because it seems that the
coalition is unwilling

00:05:19.385 --> 00:05:22.355 align:start size:84% position:16%
to utilize their
power against Assad.

00:05:22.355 --> 00:05:25.425 align:start size:84% position:16%
- Well, our American
friends here,

00:05:25.425 --> 00:05:28.094 line:0%
they have to know that we
have been fighting ISIS

00:05:28.094 --> 00:05:30.263 align:start size:84% position:16% line:0%
since the first
quarter of this year.

00:05:30.263 --> 00:05:32.699 line:0%
We have been fighting
two fronts all the way.

00:05:32.699 --> 00:05:35.401 align:start size:97% position:3% line:0%
We've been fighting ISIS and
the regime, Assad regime,

00:05:35.401 --> 00:05:38.705
at the same time with very
little help of the world.

00:05:38.705 --> 00:05:41.908
We cannot carry on the fight
on two fronts at the same time

00:05:41.908 --> 00:05:44.577
without the assistance
of our friends in the US,

00:05:44.577 --> 00:05:46.312
and other free world.

00:05:47.780 --> 00:05:49.982
- If we give you weapons,
can we put labels on them

00:05:49.982 --> 00:05:53.686
because we have a tendency
to get weapons over there,

00:05:53.686 --> 00:05:55.288
and then the bad guys
come and take them

00:05:55.288 --> 00:05:57.390
because we tend to leave.

00:05:58.524 --> 00:06:00.460
- I guess we have passed this.

00:06:00.460 --> 00:06:03.262
As you know, ISIS
has went into Iraq,

00:06:03.262 --> 00:06:05.698 align:start size:88% position:13%
and they already
captured all the weapon

00:06:05.698 --> 00:06:07.667
provided to the Iraqi armies.

00:06:07.667 --> 00:06:10.536 align:start size:97% position:3%
But for us, we are fighting
for our own freedoms.

00:06:10.536 --> 00:06:14.240 align:start size:97% position:3%
We have been handling
sophisticated weapon system,

00:06:14.240 --> 00:06:17.410
anti-tanks weapons, and
they are very well kept

00:06:17.410 --> 00:06:19.512
within the hands of
the Free Syrian Army.

00:06:19.512 --> 00:06:21.447 align:start size:88% position:13%
- Can you work also with
the Iraqi government?

00:06:21.447 --> 00:06:23.349
Will they work in
concert with you

00:06:23.349 --> 00:06:26.185 align:start size:81% position:19%
to help defeat
these two menaces,

00:06:26.185 --> 00:06:28.187
and to stabilize the region?

00:06:28.187 --> 00:06:30.656 align:start size:81% position:19%
- It's not anymore
Syrian problem.

00:06:30.656 --> 00:06:33.292
It's not anymore even
the regional problem.

00:06:33.292 --> 00:06:35.261
It is an international problem.

00:06:35.261 --> 00:06:37.797 align:start size:84% position:16%
We are talking about
an organization

00:06:37.797 --> 00:06:41.267 align:start position:0%
with 30 different nationalities
within this organization.

00:06:41.267 --> 00:06:42.735
- [Jon] Right.

00:06:42.735 --> 00:06:44.570 align:start size:97% position:3%
- You have Americans, you have
British, you have French--

00:06:44.570 --> 00:06:46.172
- Have you seen and
up-tick in support?

00:06:46.172 --> 00:06:48.875 align:start size:94% position:6%
Have you seen and up-tick
in coalition support

00:06:48.875 --> 00:06:51.544
going your way since
all this occurred?

00:06:51.544 --> 00:06:54.147
You're here for the UN mission.

00:06:54.147 --> 00:06:56.916
Are you getting the help
that you think you need,

00:06:56.916 --> 00:06:58.618
and that your people deserve?

00:06:58.618 --> 00:07:01.220 line:0%
- I think the world has started

00:07:01.220 --> 00:07:02.855 line:0%
to move in the right direction.

00:07:02.855 --> 00:07:05.825 align:start size:84% position:16% line:0%
It's not to our
expectation as of yet,

00:07:05.825 --> 00:07:10.396 align:start position:0% line:0%
but I think slowly it will
build up toward that direction.

00:07:10.396 --> 00:07:14.100
They need to notice that they
cannot eliminate terrorism

00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:16.769
by only military operations.

00:07:16.769 --> 00:07:20.573 align:start size:97% position:3%
It has to be much, much more
than military operation.

00:07:20.573 --> 00:07:22.975 align:start size:94% position:6%
You have to have a
social, political program.

00:07:22.975 --> 00:07:26.078 align:start size:88% position:13%
You need to provide a
vision of political life

00:07:26.078 --> 00:07:28.314
for all the region
in the Middle East.

00:07:28.314 --> 00:07:30.183 align:start size:84% position:16%
- I think that's the
fascinating part.

00:07:30.183 --> 00:07:31.384 align:start size:84% position:16%
Can you stick around
for a little bit?

00:07:31.384 --> 00:07:32.852
- Sure.

00:07:32.852 --> 00:07:34.353
- We'll come back, and
then I want to talk about

00:07:34.353 --> 00:07:35.955
what could work there because
it's something that I think

00:07:35.955 --> 00:07:37.857 align:start size:84% position:16%
America thought
they tried in Iraq,

00:07:37.857 --> 00:07:39.225
were not successful with.

00:07:39.225 --> 00:07:41.360 align:start size:84% position:16%
Thought they were
trying in Afghanistan,

00:07:41.360 --> 00:07:43.496
were not successful with.

00:07:43.496 --> 00:07:45.965 align:start size:84% position:16%
What a world like
that would look like,

00:07:45.965 --> 00:07:48.901
I think would be important
to find out, to delineate.

00:07:48.901 --> 00:07:50.069
Alright, so we'll be right back.

00:07:50.069 --> 00:07:51.337 align:start size:84% position:16%
Hadi al-Bahra,
we'll be right back.

00:07:51.337 --> 00:07:55.508 align:start size:84% position:16% line:0%
