(audience applauding)

00:07:59.846 --> 00:08:01.747
- We're speaking
with the President

00:08:01.747 --> 00:08:04.116
of the Syrian National
Coalition, Hadi al-Bahra.

00:08:04.116 --> 00:08:05.518
Thank you for joining us.

00:08:05.518 --> 00:08:08.387 align:start position:0%
Obviously this is a very
difficult time in your country.

00:08:08.387 --> 00:08:09.956
You are based in Turkey now.

00:08:09.956 --> 00:08:11.224
You can't be based in Syria

00:08:11.224 --> 00:08:13.292 align:start size:81% position:19%
because they would
come after you.

00:08:13.292 --> 00:08:17.396
- Yes, our head office
is in Istanbul, Turkey,

00:08:17.396 --> 00:08:20.333 align:start size:84% position:16%
but our people
exist inside Syria.

00:08:20.333 --> 00:08:23.336
We have the local councils, we
have seven different steams,

00:08:23.336 --> 00:08:26.239 align:start size:94% position:6%
we have police force
inside the liberated areas

00:08:26.239 --> 00:08:29.242
under the control
of the opposition.

00:08:31.210 --> 00:08:34.347 align:start size:97% position:3%
- What has been the reluctance
of a country like Turkey

00:08:34.347 --> 00:08:35.848 align:start size:84% position:16%
to involve themselves
in the fight,

00:08:35.848 --> 00:08:38.684
and to not close
down the borders,

00:08:40.119 --> 00:08:42.989
and to keep them so porous
in terms of black market oil

00:08:42.989 --> 00:08:45.191 align:start size:97% position:3%
going back and forth,
fighters going back and forth?

00:08:45.191 --> 00:08:50.162
How difficult is it to get
them to close that down?

00:08:50.162 --> 00:08:51.898
- You cannot look
at it this way.

00:08:51.898 --> 00:08:56.636
Turkey always faces very
hard, tough choices to make

00:08:56.636 --> 00:09:00.139
because either they go in
the strict security system,

00:09:00.139 --> 00:09:03.042
where they will not allow the
easy flow of Syrian people

00:09:03.042 --> 00:09:07.346 align:start size:97% position:3%
out of Syria, inside
Syria, and food and supply.

00:09:07.346 --> 00:09:10.483
The other option is to let
the humanitarian convoys

00:09:10.483 --> 00:09:13.953
and the free movement of
the Syrian people easier.

00:09:13.953 --> 00:09:17.757
Always Turkey chose to stay
on the humanitarian side

00:09:17.757 --> 00:09:21.327
of the problem, risking
its own even security.

00:09:21.327 --> 00:09:23.329
But today, as we
heard in the news,

00:09:23.329 --> 00:09:26.899
that Mr. Erdogan has announced
his support to the coalition,

00:09:26.899 --> 00:09:29.068 align:start size:84% position:16%
and he said Turkey
cannot stay any longer

00:09:29.068 --> 00:09:30.836
outside of this coalition.

00:09:30.836 --> 00:09:34.840 align:start position:0%
- So you believe we have reached
a certain coalescence point

00:09:34.840 --> 00:09:37.376 align:start size:88% position:13%
where the world will
take this seriously now,

00:09:37.376 --> 00:09:41.180
and it will change
things on the ground?

00:09:41.180 --> 00:09:42.715
- It has to be changed.

00:09:42.715 --> 00:09:44.917 align:start size:84% position:16%
It's a risk you
cannot ignore anymore.

00:09:44.917 --> 00:09:47.587
Should we wait until we
see these guys all over

00:09:47.587 --> 00:09:49.956 align:start size:84% position:16%
in the United
States, or in Europe?

00:09:49.956 --> 00:09:51.924
We are your front line.

00:09:51.924 --> 00:09:53.993
We have been fighting as I said,

00:09:53.993 --> 00:09:56.529 align:start size:84% position:16%
from the first quarter
of this year alone.

00:09:56.529 --> 00:10:01.000 align:start size:97% position:3%
Isn't it enough, or about time
now for you to support us?

00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:03.202 align:start size:84% position:16%
Now you are supporting
with the weapons,

00:10:03.202 --> 00:10:06.005
with supplies, with
the humanitarian aid

00:10:06.005 --> 00:10:09.875 align:start size:88% position:13%
which you should do more
aggressively with us

00:10:09.875 --> 00:10:13.713
because we are the front line
in the war against terrorism.

00:10:13.713 --> 00:10:16.616 align:start size:84% position:16%
- Is it difficult
as you observe this,

00:10:16.616 --> 00:10:20.786
to watch our Congress not
come back from their break

00:10:23.055 --> 00:10:24.590
to talk about it?

00:10:24.590 --> 00:10:27.159
Is that seem like an abdication

00:10:28.327 --> 00:10:31.664 align:start size:84% position:16%
of a responsibility
in your eyes?

00:10:31.664 --> 00:10:35.434
- For us, I mean we look at
our own national interests,

00:10:35.434 --> 00:10:37.970
and our way of life,
as the American people,

00:10:37.970 --> 00:10:40.339 align:start size:81% position:19%
they don't feel
the danger of this

00:10:40.339 --> 00:10:43.743
because it's far away
from their homeland.

00:10:43.743 --> 00:10:46.612
But for us, we can
foresee its problem

00:10:46.612 --> 00:10:50.049
to our national interest, to
the region, and to the world.

00:10:50.049 --> 00:10:52.051
So we should I think, all of us,

00:10:52.051 --> 00:10:54.153 align:start size:84% position:16%
we should be more
responsible in this.

00:10:54.153 --> 00:10:56.455
- What does a stable
situation look like?

00:10:56.455 --> 00:10:58.190
Because the entire region,

00:10:58.190 --> 00:11:00.192
I mean you can distill
the conflict in Syria,

00:11:00.192 --> 00:11:01.794
but the entire region
is sort of trapped

00:11:01.794 --> 00:11:05.331 align:start size:84% position:16%
between these despots,
and terrorists.

00:11:05.331 --> 00:11:08.534
You have autocracies, and you
have these Islamist groups

00:11:08.534 --> 00:11:10.302 align:start size:94% position:6%
that are bringing
terror, and it seems like

00:11:10.302 --> 00:11:12.304
there's a large majority
of people in the middle

00:11:12.304 --> 00:11:14.573 align:start size:84% position:16%
that are caught
between this fight.

00:11:14.573 --> 00:11:16.509
- No, for us as Syrian people,

00:11:16.509 --> 00:11:19.979 align:start size:84% position:16%
we seek democracy
and freedom for all.

00:11:19.979 --> 00:11:24.016
We seek protection of
all the Syrian people.

00:11:24.016 --> 00:11:26.619 align:start size:88% position:13%
You know Syria is
unique in its position.

00:11:26.619 --> 00:11:30.022 align:start size:97% position:3%
We have many ethnicity,
many religious in our land.

00:11:30.022 --> 00:11:33.426 align:start size:88% position:13%
Syrian society is
open, moderate society.

00:11:34.560 --> 00:11:36.328 align:start size:84% position:16%
Syria's the only
country in the world

00:11:36.328 --> 00:11:38.130
where you have people who speak

00:11:38.130 --> 00:11:40.900 align:start size:84% position:16%
in the tongue of
Jesus, until to now.

00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:44.570
If we were extremist country,
you wouldn't find these guys.

00:11:44.570 --> 00:11:46.138
- No, no, no.

00:11:46.138 --> 00:11:49.875
That's my point, I think is
that it's a moderate people,

00:11:49.875 --> 00:11:53.913
but they're trapped between
extremists and authoritarian.

00:11:53.913 --> 00:11:55.815 align:start size:88% position:13%
- I think the whole
region will have to move

00:11:55.815 --> 00:11:59.085
into more democratic
type of government

00:12:00.352 --> 00:12:02.521
procedure and systems.

00:12:02.521 --> 00:12:04.256
I think it will move.

00:12:04.256 --> 00:12:07.059
It started already
in Tunisia, in Egypt,

00:12:07.059 --> 00:12:08.694
and other countries.

00:12:08.694 --> 00:12:12.698
Nobody can move against
the movement of history.

00:12:13.899 --> 00:12:16.368
I think Syria will
be the cornerstone

00:12:16.368 --> 00:12:18.804
of democracy in the region.

00:12:18.804 --> 00:12:22.441 align:start size:97% position:3%
- And your group is working
to rebuild that civil society.

00:12:22.441 --> 00:12:25.611
Have you created enough of
a free zone for yourselves,

00:12:25.611 --> 00:12:28.414 align:start size:88% position:13%
that there's at least
some semblance of safety

00:12:28.414 --> 00:12:30.015
for at least that group?

00:12:30.015 --> 00:12:32.451 align:start size:84% position:16%
- As you know, until
now we don't have

00:12:32.451 --> 00:12:34.320
a free zone inside Syria.

00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:37.990 align:start size:97% position:3%
We control land, but we don't
have air defense for it,

00:12:37.990 --> 00:12:41.427
so daily these areas been
bombarded by Assad regime

00:12:41.427 --> 00:12:44.597
using TNT barrels,
all type of bombs.

00:12:44.597 --> 00:12:46.031
- So if they did a no-fly zone,

00:12:46.031 --> 00:12:48.000 align:start size:84% position:16%
would that be at
least the first step?

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:50.302
Create a no-fly zone over Syria?

00:12:50.302 --> 00:12:52.772
- This should be the
first thing to consider

00:12:52.772 --> 00:12:56.208
in order to provide this
swift transition of power

00:12:56.208 --> 00:12:59.445
inside Syria and allow
people chance to live

00:12:59.445 --> 00:13:01.847
a little normally in
the liberated area,

00:13:01.847 --> 00:13:04.817 align:start size:88% position:13%
and to start, look,
and build their future.

00:13:04.817 --> 00:13:08.721 align:start size:97% position:3%
- Is the drawback to that,
that Iran will not allow that,

00:13:08.721 --> 00:13:10.256 align:start size:84% position:16%
or that Russia will
not allow that?

00:13:10.256 --> 00:13:13.325
Who is standing in the way of
a no-fly zone over that area?

00:13:13.325 --> 00:13:17.563 align:start size:94% position:6%
- Well I think only Russia
and Iran are the front

00:13:17.563 --> 00:13:19.732
opposing this no-fly zone.

00:13:21.634 --> 00:13:23.469
- Okay, so we have
to go to a war with,

00:13:23.469 --> 00:13:24.303
alright, hold on.

00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:25.604
Let me work this out.

00:13:25.604 --> 00:13:28.174
I'm just working out this math.

00:13:29.441 --> 00:13:31.744 align:start size:84% position:16%
- I don't think
they will go to war.

00:13:31.744 --> 00:13:34.547
If you remember when
the chemical attack

00:13:34.547 --> 00:13:37.483
which Assad carried out
against his own people,

00:13:37.483 --> 00:13:39.819
and 1,400 people died.

00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:40.653
- Yes.

00:13:40.653 --> 00:13:42.922
- The US put a red line,

00:13:42.922 --> 00:13:45.658 align:start size:81% position:19%
and threatened
about using force.

00:13:46.525 --> 00:13:48.060
- Yes.

00:13:48.060 --> 00:13:50.963
- When Assad felt that the US
is serious about using force,

00:13:50.963 --> 00:13:53.699
he backed out, and he
signed the agreement

00:13:53.699 --> 00:13:57.002
to disarm and let go
of his chemical weapon.

00:13:57.002 --> 00:14:00.673
Russia at that time, said
they are not ready to fight

00:14:00.673 --> 00:14:02.842
for any regime in the area.

00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:05.344
So all what we need,
we need the resolve

00:14:05.344 --> 00:14:07.613
by the US and by our friends,

00:14:07.613 --> 00:14:10.516 align:start size:88% position:13%
and really to tell
Assad enough is enough.

00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:14.720
If we treat the sole cause,
for sure we'll be 50% away

00:14:14.720 --> 00:14:17.056
in our fight against terrorism.

00:14:17.056 --> 00:14:19.992 align:start size:88% position:13%
- And you feel this will
not trigger or create

00:14:19.992 --> 00:14:22.228
a deeper fault line
between the Sunni

00:14:22.228 --> 00:14:23.495
and the Shiite community?

00:14:23.495 --> 00:14:24.897
You don't feel like
that will trigger--

00:14:24.897 --> 00:14:27.132
- It is not a sectarian war.

00:14:27.132 --> 00:14:30.970
It is Assad tried to make
it as a sectarian war.

00:14:30.970 --> 00:14:32.571
He had tried to ignite it.

00:14:32.571 --> 00:14:34.773
Until now, he could not.

00:14:34.773 --> 00:14:35.808
- Well I wish you all the best.

00:14:35.808 --> 00:14:37.610
I know you have a book.

00:14:37.610 --> 00:14:40.546
- I have one bracelet which
I've been asked to give you.

00:14:40.546 --> 00:14:41.647
- So we're going steady now?

00:14:41.647 --> 00:14:42.748
I think is what's happening.

00:14:42.748 --> 00:14:43.716
(laughing)

00:14:43.716 --> 00:14:44.984
We are.

00:14:44.984 --> 00:14:47.419
This is what's remarkable.

00:14:47.419 --> 00:14:48.621
I want to get to this.

00:14:48.621 --> 00:14:50.890
- I have this great
book to remember

00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:55.661 align:start position:0%
the first 100,000 people killed
in Syria by Assad regime.

00:14:55.661 --> 00:14:58.497 align:start size:88% position:13%
This project was carried
out with the dream

00:14:58.497 --> 00:15:02.601
